In the context described, the target genes involved are the StNF-YA (Nuclear Factor Y, subunit A) genes in potato. These genes are transcription factors that play a crucial role in regulating various processes related to plant development and stress responses. The mature stu-miR169 family members specifically target the StNF-YA genes, leading to their down-regulation under normal conditions. During drought stress, the expression of stu-miR169 is decreased, which allows for the over-expression of the StNF-YA genes, thereby contributing to the plant’s adaptive response to drought stress.
Pathway: e miR169/NF-YA module, which is part of the broader regulatory network of gene expression in plants under stress conditions.
